<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,951,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,951,975]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[536,638,952,975]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,275,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[201,1375,365,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[201,1375,357,1854]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. terminalia of male Haplaxius species from the Dominican Republic. 1 – 3, H. cabrerensis, n. sp., holotype. Male terminalia in left lateral, right lateral, and ventral views, respectively. 4 – 6, H. jamaicae (Kramer). Male terminalia in left lateral, right lateral, and ventral views, respectively. 7, H. crudus (Van Duzee). Habitus, dorsal view; af, “ anal flap ” of Kramer (abdominal segment X); ml, median lobe of pygofer (pyg); tri, diagnostic subtriangular projection. All images are of specimens from the Dominican Republic." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197881/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Figs. 
<number box="[597,638,952,975]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin subtriangular, abdominal segment X with singular, triangular process distoventrally. Aedeagus with a small, serrate, apical process directed dorsally, and a long narrow process directed anteriorly. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[645,709,1016,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,275,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[201,1375,365,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[201,1375,357,1854]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. terminalia of male Haplaxius species from the Dominican Republic. 1 – 3, H. cabrerensis, n. sp., holotype. Male terminalia in left lateral, right lateral, and ventral views, respectively. 4 – 6, H. jamaicae (Kramer). Male terminalia in left lateral, right lateral, and ventral views, respectively. 7, H. crudus (Van Duzee). Habitus, dorsal view; af, “ anal flap ” of Kramer (abdominal segment X); ml, median lobe of pygofer (pyg); tri, diagnostic subtriangular projection. All images are of specimens from the Dominican Republic." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197881/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[695,709,1016,1039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) distally capitate but elongate. Color uniformly pale brown without distinct color pattern; forewings hyaline with veins pale brown.
</paragraph>
